    data = response.json()
    print(data)
else:
    print("API request failed:", response.status_code)


ğŸ‘‰ Your API_KEY is usually stored in a .env or config file (not in code) for security.

ğŸ§© 7ï¸âƒ£ Making a Response API (Your Own)

If you want to create an API, you use frameworks like Flask or FastAPI.

Example (Flask mini API):

